fields.description:
when you edit previously saved issue with the characters like *<* or *>* converts to < >

For example, if I have some text like:

DB fields:

{code}
product->title
product->desc
{code}

When I open the Issue tracker and edit this text again, all {{>}} will be converted to {{>}}

‌

PS. I’ve attached the screen recording

When using a github repository as a package.

Example, lets say you’re using the following as a dependency

{code}
"dependencies": {
  "thrones": "john_snow/game_of_thrones#master",
}
{code}

and you change the dependancy branch to _starks_killed_

{code}
"dependencies": {
  "thrones": "john_snow/game_of_thrones#starks_killed",
}
{code}

The cache on the build pipeline won’t be invalidated. If you clear the cache it works fine.
